HEADWORD: Cassel earth
<hw>Cas"sel earth</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A brown pigment of varying permanence, consisting of
impure lignite. It was found originally near <etsep>Cassel</etsep> (now
Kassel), Germany.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

